aniel O&apos;Connell|Daniel O&apos;Connell - \"The Liberator\"]]\ncircle 2375 1062 35 [[#Victuallers|William Fairbank]]\ncircle 2439 1050 44 [[#Victuallers|John Woodmark]]\ncircle 2515 1056 41 [[William Smeal|William Smeal from Glasgow]]\ncircle 2345 1170 58 [[James Carlile|James Carlile - Irish Minister and educationalist]]\ncircle 2436 1158 58 [[Thomas Binney |Rev. Dr. Thomas Binney ]]\ncircle 2497 1173 58 [[Edward Barrett (freedman)|Edward Barrett - Freed slave]]\ncircle 2559 1176 58 [[John Howard Hinton|John Howard Hinton - Baptist minister]]\ncircle 2623 1202 58 [[John Angell James|John Angell James - clergyman]]\ncircle 2685 1313 64 [[#Victuallers|Joseph Cooper]]\ncircle 2685 1100 47 [[Richard Robert Madden|Dr. Richard Robert Madden - Irish]]\ncircle 2749 1053 35 [[#Victuallers|Thomas Bulley]]\ncircle 2816 1067 35 [[#Victuallers|Isaac Hodgson]]\ncircle 2869 1053 35 [[#Victuallers|Edward Smith]]\ncircle 2819 1290 58 [[John Bowring|Sir John Bowring - diplomat and linguist]]\ncircle 2854 1149 44 [[John Ellis (businessman)|John Ellis]]\ncircle 2904 1296 58 [[Charles Edwards Lester|C. Edwards Lester - American writer]]\ncircle 3041 1015 35 [[Richard Tapper Cadbury|Tapper Cadbury - Businessman]]\ncircle 2936 1170 58 [[#Victuallers|not known]]\ncircle 2968 1070 41 [[#Victuallers|Thomas Pinches ]]\ncircle 3027 1155 47 [[David Turnbull (British abolitionist)|David Turnbull - Cuban link]]\ncircle 3000 1076 35 [[Edward Adey]]\ncircle 3050 1237 58 [[#Victuallers|Richard Barrett]]\ncircle 3114 1164 47 [[#Victuallers|John Steer]]\ncircle 2974 1287 58 [[#Victuallers|Henry Tuckett ]]\ncircle 3185 1164 58 [[James Mott|James Mott - American on honeymoon]]\nrect 2872 1395 2959 1547 [[William Forster (philanthropist)|Robert Forster (brother of William and Josiah)]]\ncircle 3103 1064 58 [[Richard Rathbone]]\ncircle 3208 1064 58 [[#Victuallers|John Birt]]\ncircle 3021 1354 58 [[Wendell Phillips|Wendell Phillips - American]]\ncircle 3012 1491 88 [[#Victuallers|M. L&apos;Instant from Haiti]]\ncircle 3113 1489 111 [[Henry Stanton|Henry Stanton - American]]\ncircle 3237 980 58 [[William Adam (Professor)|Prof William Adam]]\ncircle 3398 950 58 [[John Harfield Tredgold|Mrs Elizabeth Tredgold - British South African]]\ncircle 3346 1035 58 [[#Victuallers|T.M. McDonnell ]]\ncircle 3427 1047 58 [[#Victuallers|Mrs John Beaumont]]\ncircle 3473 1286 58 [[Anne Knight|Anne Knight - Feminist]]\ncircle 3565 1116 85 [[Elizabeth Pease Nichol|Elizabeth Pease - Suffragist]]\ncircle 3138 1307 64 [[Jacob Post|Jacob Post - Religious writer]]\ncircle 3223 1296 58 [[Lady Byron|Anne Isabella, Lady Byron - mathematician and estranged wife]]\ncircle 3305 1291 76 [[Amelia Opie|Amelia Opie - Novelist and poet]]\ncircle 3506 1278 105 [[Mary Anne Rawson|Mrs Rawson - Sheffield campaigner]]\ncircle 395 1208 58 [[Thomas Clarkson|Thomas Clarkson&apos;s grandson Thomas Clarkson]]\ncircle 2778 1141 58 [[#Victuallers|Thomas Morgan]]\npoly 839 1211 885 1108 916 1007 969 950 1031 918 1073 881 1051 861 1053 798 1105 751 1185 745 1240 792 1236 838 1212 890 1205 915 1217 933 1273 950 1339 934 1414 863 1471 776 1467 741 1472 701 1489 700 1496 661 1509 661 1511 719 1518 705 1556 736 1524 806 1528 814 1447 966 1407 1008 1356 1029 1263 1054 1238 1119 1214 1212 840 1212 840 1212 [[Thomas Clarkson|Thomas Clarkson - main speaker]]\npoly 2943 2001 2919 1901 2971 1823 3054 1807 3140 1827 3167 1743 3238 1636 3271 1601 3272 1572 3266 1559 3293 1530 3293 1498 3332 1440 3377 1435 3427 1453 3471 1484 3483 1541 3459 1612 3443 1626 3441 1672 3476 1712 3531 1745 3546 1776 3546 1850 3553 1923 3519 2005 3265 1918 3207 1942 3216 2008 2947 2008 2947 2008 [[George Head Head|George Head Head - Banker from Carlisle]]\npoly 924 2026 899 1933 850 1861 756 1820 726 1809 778 1696 833 1641 913 1582 908 1553 908 1524 958 1483 1017 1463 1063 1461 1135 1495 1144 1523 1127 1541 1122 1585 1131 1613 1133 1631 1114 1632 1117 1650 1108 1670 1101 1690 1080 1697 1109 1737 1177 1729 1285 1834 1299 1912 1268 1956 1256 1967 122