<li id="mwD2Q"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt2535" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"first":{"wt":"Kevin"},"last":{"wt":"Bales"},"title":{"wt":"Ending Slavery: How We Free Today&apos;s Slaves"},"url":{"wt":"{{google books |plainurl=y |id=6Tf5xKoQQYcC}}"},"date":{"wt":"2007"},"publisher":{"wt":"University of California Press"},"isbn":{"wt":"978-0-520-25470-1"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwD2U">Bales, Kevin (2007). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=6Tf5xKoQQYcC"><i>Ending Slavery: How We Free Today's Slaves</i></a>. University of California Press. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-520-25470-1" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-520-25470-1">978-0-520-25470-1</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Ending+Slavery%3A+How+We+Free+Today%27s+Slaves&amp;rft.pub=University+of+California+Press&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-520-25470-1&amp;rft.aulast=Bales&amp;rft.aufirst=Kevin&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D6Tf5xKoQQYcC&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASlavery" class="Z3988" about="#mwt2535"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt2535" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}'/></li>
<li id="mwD2Y"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt2536" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"first1":{"wt":"Mende"},"last1":{"wt":"Nazer"},"first2":{"wt":"Damien"},"last2":{"wt":"Lewis"},"title":{"wt":"Slave: My True Story"},"url":{"wt":"{{google books |plainurl=y |id=hSGqFr-YUNkC}}"},"date":{"wt":"2009"},"publisher":{"wt":"PublicAffairs"},"isbn":{"wt":"978-0-7867-3897-7"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwD2c">Nazer, Mende; Lewis, Damien (2009). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=hSGqFr-YUNkC"><i>Slave: My True Story</i></a>. PublicAffairs. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-7867-3897-7" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-7867-3897-7">978-0-7867-3897-7</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Slave%3A+My+True+Story&amp;rft.pub=PublicAffairs&amp;rft.date=2009&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-7867-3897-7&amp;rft.aulast=Nazer&amp;rft.aufirst=Mende&amp;rft.au=Lewis%2C+Damien&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DhSGqFr-YUNkC&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASlavery" class="Z3988" about="#mwt2536"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt2536" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}'/> Mende is a <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Nuba" title="Nuba" id="mwD2g" class="mw-redirect">Nuba</a>, captured at 12 years old. She was granted <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Right_of_asylum" title="Right of asylum" id="mwD2k">political asylum</a> by the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Government_of_the_United_Kingdom" title="Government of the United